DICOM: Types and relations

Classes | Datatype Properties

Classes

dicom:'Tag'

dicom:'Tag' has attributes:
  • Label: 'Tag'
  • Definition: A unique identifier for an element of information composed of an ordered pair of numbers (a Group Number followed by an Element Number), which is used to identify Attributes and corresponding Data Elements.
  • dicom:'Tag' is a obo:IAO_0020000.
  • Type: owl:Class
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

Datatype Properties

dicom:'File-set ID'

dicom:'File-set ID' has attributes:
  • Label: 'File-set ID'
  • Definition: User or implementation specific Identifier (up to 16 characters). The File-set ID is intended to be a short human readable label to easily (but not necessarily uniquely) identify a specific File-set to facilitate operator manipulation of the physical media on which the File-set is stored. Assignment of Value and semantics are environment specific.
  • dicom:'File-set ID' is a nidm:DICOMTag.
  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'File-set Descriptor File ID'

dicom:'File-set Descriptor File ID' has attributes:
  • Label: 'File-set Descriptor File ID'
  • Definition: ID of a File (in the same File-set) used for user comments related to the File-set (e.g., a README file). The Specific Character set used may be specified in the Specific Character Set of the File-set Descriptor File (0004,1142). This File is not DICOM formatted (no Preamble, nor DICM Prefix and Meta Information).
  • dicom:'File-set Descriptor File ID' is a nidm:DICOMTag.
  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Specific Character Set of File-set Descriptor File'

dicom:'Specific Character Set of File-set Descriptor File' has attributes:
  • Label: 'Specific Character Set of File-set Descriptor File'
  • Definition: Character set used in the File-set Descriptor File with a File ID as specified in File-set Descriptor File ID (0004,1141). Required to specify the expanded or replacement character set.
  • dicom:'Specific Character Set of File-set Descriptor File' is a nidm:DICOMTag.
  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Offset of the First Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity'

dicom:'Offset of the First Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity' has attributes:
  • Label: 'Offset of the First Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity'
  • Definition: Offset of the first byte (of the Item Data Element) of the first Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity. This Offset is a number of bytes starting with the first byte of the File Meta Information. When the Root Directory Entity contains no Directory Record, this offset shall be set to 00000000H. This offset includes the File Preamble and the DICM Prefix.
  • dicom:'Offset of the First Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity' is a nidm:DICOMTag.
  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Offset of the Last Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity'

dicom:'Offset of the Last Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity' has attributes:
  • Label: 'Offset of the Last Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity'
  • Definition: Offset of the first byte (of the Item Data Element) of the last Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity. This Offset is a number of bytes starting with the first byte of the File Meta Information. When the Root Directory Entity contains no Directory Record, this offset shall be set to 00000000H. This offset includes the File Preamble and the DICM Prefix.
  • dicom:'Offset of the Last Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity' is a nidm:DICOMTag.
  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'File-set Consistency Flag'

dicom:'File-set Consistency Flag' has attributes:
  • Label: 'File-set Consistency Flag'
  • Definition: Enumerated Values: 0000H no known inconsistencies The value FFFFH shall never be present. Formerly, this Attribute was intended to signal that the directory was in an inconsistent state with a value of FFFFH. This usage has been retired.
  • dicom:'File-set Consistency Flag' is a nidm:DICOMTag.
  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Directory Record Sequence'

dicom:'Directory Record Sequence' has attributes:
  • Label: 'Directory Record Sequence'
  • Definition: Sequence of zero or more Items where each Item contains a Directory Record by including the Directory Elements from (0004,1400) to (0004,1511) and Record selection Keys as defined below (marked with a >). A zero length Value indicates that no Directory Records are contained in the Root Directory Entity.
  • dicom:'Directory Record Sequence' is a nidm:DICOMTag.
  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Offset of the Next Directory Record'

dicom:'Offset of the Next Directory Record' has attributes:
  • Label: 'Offset of the Next Directory Record'
  • Definition: Offset of the first byte (of the Item Data Element) of the next Directory Record of the same Directory Entity. This Offset is an unsigned integer representing a number of bytes starting with the first byte of the File Meta-information. A zero offset shall be used to mean that there is no other Directory Record in this Directory Entity. This Offset may be used to keep an inactive Record (0004,1410) chained with the next Directory Record of the same Directory Entity. This offset includes the File Preamble and the DICM Prefix.
  • dicom:'Offset of the Next Directory Record' is a nidm:DICOMTag.
  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Record In-use Flag'

dicom:'Record In-use Flag' has attributes:
  • Label: 'Record In-use Flag'
  • Definition: A flag that indicates whether or not a record is in use.
  • dicom:'Record In-use Flag' is a nidm:DICOMTag.
  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Offset of Referenced Lower-Level Directory Entity'

dicom:'Offset of Referenced Lower-Level Directory Entity' has attributes:
  • Label: 'Offset of Referenced Lower-Level Directory Entity'
  • Definition: Offset of the first byte (of the Item Data Element) of the first Directory Record of the Referenced Lower Level Directory Entity. This Offset is a number of bytes starting with the first byte of the File Meta Information. When no lower-level Directory Entity (containing at least one Directory Record) is referenced, this Attribute shall have a Value of 00000000H. This offset includes the File Preamble and the DICM Prefix.
  • dicom:'Offset of Referenced Lower-Level Directory Entity' is a nidm:DICOMTag.
  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Private Record UID'

dicom:'Private Record UID' has attributes:
  • Label: 'Private Record UID'
  • Definition: Required if the Directory Record Type (0004,1430) is of Value PRIVATE. This UID is used to define a non-standard type of Directory Record by reference to its position in a private extension to the Basic Directory IOD Information Model.
  • dicom:'Private Record UID' is a nidm:DICOMTag.
  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Referenced File ID'

dicom:'Referenced File ID' has attributes:
  • Label: 'Referenced File ID'
  • Definition: A Multiple Value that represents the ordered components of the File ID containing a 'referenced object' or Referenced SOP Instance. A maximum of 8 components, each from 1 to 8 characters shall be used. The Referenced File ID provides the means to 'locate' the File through the DICOM File Service provided by the Media Format Layer. All referenced Files shall be with the File-set to which the Directory belongs. Any File within the File-set (to which the Directory belongs) shall be referenced by at most one Directory Record.
  • dicom:'Referenced File ID' is a nidm:DICOMTag.
  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

This attribute is not intended for conveying localizer reference information, for which Referenced Image Sequence (0008,1140) should be used.

  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

This allows recognition that images and spectra in different instances have been reconstructed from the same raw data. For such items the SOP Class UID would be '1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.66' (Raw Data SOP Class) and the SOP Instance UID would be any appropriate UID.

The diameter defines a circular region that is entirely contained within the encoded Pixel Data (7FE0,0010), unless the encoded image has been cropped after reconstruction. If not cropped or padded, for square images with square pixels, both values of Pixel Spacing (0028,0030) will be equal and equal to Reconstruction Diameter (0018,1100) / Rows (0028,0010) and Reconstruction Diameter (0018,1100) / Columns (0028,0011).

  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

  • Definition: Determined from the curvature (2nd derivative = d2y/dx2) of a point on the cornea, in diopters; also called Instantaneous Power. Emphasizes irregular astigmatism (large variations in higher order aberrations).
  • dicom:'Tangential Power' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

  • Definition: Conveys the optical refraction properties of the cornea, in diopters. It is determined from ray tracing using Snells Law to calculate the true refractive power. It is used to evaluate ocular optics.
  • dicom:'Refractive Power' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

This value is determined from z - zref. Where z is conveyed in Attribute Corneal Point Location (0046,0247) and zref is the elevation of the reference surface.

  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

This permits measurement of both low and higher order aberrations and provides the total amount of distortion of the Corneal Wavefront with a Root Mean Square (RMS) value.

dicom:'Abstract Prior Value'

dicom:'Abstract Prior Value' has attributes:
  • Label: 'Abstract Prior Value'
  • Definition: Identifies a prior image set in abstract terms. Exactly two integer values, indicating the range of prior studies to include. Each value shall be greater than zero, where 1 indicates the most recent prior and higher values indicate successively older priors. The special value -1 shall indicate the oldest prior. The value pair n,n indicates the nth prior. The value pair -1/-1 indicates the oldest prior. The value pair m/n indicates the mth through nth priors, where m is the more recent prior. The value pair 1/-1 indicates all priors. The value pair m/-1 indicates the mth prior and all priors older than m. Required if Image Set Selector Category (0072,0034) is ABSTRACT_PRIOR and Abstract Prior Code Sequence (0072,003E) is not present.
  • dicom:'Abstract Prior Value' is a nidm:DICOMTag.
  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Overlay Origin'

dicom:'Overlay Origin' has attributes:
  • Label: 'Overlay Origin'
  • Definition: Location of first overlay point with respect to pixels in the image, given as row/column. The upper left pixel of the image has the coordinate 1/1. Column values greater than 1 indicate the overlay plane origin is to the right of the image origin. Row values greater than 1 indicate the overlay plane origin is below the image origin. Values less than 1 indicate the overlay plane origin is above or to the left of the image origin. Values of 0/0 indicate that the overlay pixels start 1 row above and one column to the left of the image pixels.
  • dicom:'Overlay Origin' is a nidm:DICOMTag.
  • Type: owl:DatatypeProperty
  • Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428
